modules.description: Provides pattern matching with transformation by applying an expression to a value before matching against a pattern. Works with OCaml's pattern syntax and expressions, enabling custom matching logic within match cases. Enables concise handling of transformed values in pattern guards, such as matching on the result of a function applied to an input.

Extracts pattern matching information from type definitions, enabling custom syntax for pattern matching. Works with OCaml's abstract syntax tree and viewpattern annotations. Used to generate boilerplate code for complex pattern matching scenarios.
